lt;p>This publication provides an examination on the costs and governance of large scale HIV prevention programmes in Southern India. A first set of papers uses statistical techniques to look at the relationship between coverage and cost of HIV prevention services and examines the nature of transaction costs in HIV prevention programmes delivering services by contracting with large numbers of NGOs.&amp;nbsp;The second set of papers uses alternative methodologies to look at both the efficiency of HIV prevention projects at different levels of scale and the nature of contractual relationships. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The fellowship includes support for further training in health economics, the efficiency of health services and qualitative research analysis, professional meetings for those working in the fields of health economics and HIV/AIDS and the dissemination of the research results in a number of fora. &lt;br />&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2009-03-13</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2007-07-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>31183</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs><gtr:impactSummaryOutput><gtr:description>The postdoctoral award was terminated early for personal reasons before new findings were generated. Publications generated during the award period have been cited in work on the Gates Avahan initiative for HIV prevention in Southern India and contributed to the development of methodological techniques in estimating cost functions for public health programmes in low and middle income countries and work on contracting for health services in these settings.</gtr:description><gtr:firstYearOfImpact>2011</gtr:firstYearOfImpact><gtr:id>0D15D771-BC5F-434D-8D8E-E5447D173224</gtr:id><gtr:impactTypes><gtr:impactType>Policy &amp; public services</gtr:impactType></gtr:impactTypes><gtr:outcomeId>545a2ad04de476.70957995</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sector>Healthcare</gtr:sector></gtr:impactSummaryOutput></gtr:impactSummaryOutputs><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:description>The postdoc research grant enabled me to examine further issues around costs of large scale HIV prevention programmes in Southern India. We examined how delivery costs might change as activities are scaled up and demonstrated using econometric methods that economies of scale do exist for these programmes. In addition, we documented the nature of contractual relationships between government organisations and their NGO counterparts responsible for delivering services. This helped to explain the importance of strong monitoring systems and trust between organisations in delivering effective programmes.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>Government and donor organisations working on contracting out with NGO partners, in particular in South Asia, will find the conclusions relevant to shaping their contractual relationships with partners.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>55E6F9B7-A34F-4552-85D1-030A1709DEC2</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>545a2a5a573cc2.58970205</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Healthcare,Government, Democracy and Justice</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors><gtr:url>http://researchonline.lshtm.ac.uk/1567779/</gtr:url></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>A760919A-C010-48D4-8E7B-9CDC0EAC00C6</gtr:id><gtr:title>A cost function for HIV prevention services: is there a 'u' - shape?</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Cost effectiveness and resource allocation : C/E</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/c7118a725df21e9e0c12e4d9a8580ec7"><gtr:id>c7118a725df21e9e0c12e4d9a8580ec7</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Guinness L</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2007-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>1478-7547</gtr:issn><gtr:outcomeId>doi_53cfabfab83e7b5c</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication></gtr:publications><gtr:identifiers><gtr:identifier type="RCUK">ES/E023762/1</gtr:identifier></gtr:identifiers><gtr:healthCategories/><gtr:researchActivities/><gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:res